latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Follow along with us and give this full body workout a go! All you need is a mat, a towel and some water (to stay hydrated) and you're ready! The intensity of the workout depends on how much you want to challenge yourself and please use the modifications mentioned when needed. The most important part about working out and staying fit is being grateful for where your body is at right now and being thankful for having the ability and privilege to move. Hope you guys give this workout a go! More full length workouts coming up so stay tuned. :)

On a serious note…
If you’re not doing Farmer’s Carries, you’re leaving strength on the table.

💥 Benefits of Farmer’s Carry:
✔️ Builds unreal grip strength
✔️ Improves posture & core stability
✔️ Boosts shoulder & trap development
✔️ Enhances functional strength (real-world power)
✔️ Great for conditioning without pounding your joints
✔️ Teaches you to brace and breathe under load

Whether you’re an athlete, actor, or just want to feel unshakable—start carrying heavy things and watch your body level up. 💪

Getting better at pull ups one rep at a time🔥 

If you’re able to knock out a few solid reps on the assisted pull up machine, now’s the time to level up with negatives ⬇️. Start at the top, lower yourself down slow and controlled, and build that raw strength! 💪🏽 

Pull ups can feel intimidating especially for women — but that’s exactly why we should lean into them 🧠. 
They train your upper body 💥 core grip strength ✊ and mental toughness too. 
More importantly they help us overcome that voice that whispers “you’re not strong enough” 😤

If a movement makes you feel weak, that’s not a reason to quit, it’s a sign to keep going✨. Every rep is a reminder that you’re capable of more than you think. You don’t need to do a perfect pull up today (I know I’m definitely not even CLOSE!) just show up, hang, pull and fight for it! 

Your future self will thank you 🙏 
Tag a strong woman who’s on this journey too 💥🫶
